article_title: Germany, Austria Scramble to Absorb Wave of Migrants
article_text:
BERLIN—Germany and Austria scrambled to quickly absorb thousands of new migrants arriving this weekend after the two countries agreed to allow people stranded in Hungary to cross its borders.

By late Saturday, about 6,500 migrants had entered the Burgenland region in Austria close to the Hungarian border, according to a spokesman for the Austrian interior ministry. Roughly 1,000 were granted temporary shelter in the border town of...

BERLIN—Germany and Austria scrambled to quickly absorb thousands of new migrants arriving this weekend after the two countries agreed to allow people stranded in Hungary to cross its borders.
By late Saturday, about 6,500 migrants had entered the Burgenland region in Austria close to the Hungarian border, according to a spokesman for the Austrian interior ministry.
